post_text:
Classroom Welcome Videos and Health Screenings

Evergreen Families,

We can't wait for Monday! Below are some final updates and reminders as we prepare to welcome students on-site.

Classroom Welcome Videos
Since we cannot host a traditional Student Experience Day this year, teachers will be calling families and making classroom welcome videos. Classroom Welcome Videos will be posted over the next few days.

Daily Health Screenings from Home
Please carefully read page 19 of our COVID-19 Guidelines and Procedures regarding screening your child each day before school. If your child can answer "Yes" to any of the health screening questions, please keep your child at home.

Remember to WWW!
Help protect yourself and others, Wolverines!
Wash your hands!
Watch your distance!
Wear your face covering!

Thank you again to everyone for your continued patience, flexibility, and grace.

See you Monday!
Best regards,
Laurie

ATTENTION EVERGREEN FAMILIES: North Valley Food Bank Mobile Pantry TIME AND LOCATION CHANGE!

Starting this week, NVFB will distribute food at Evergreen Junior High every Wednesday 10:30AM - 11AM

New customers welcome! No eligibility requirements or supporting documentation needed.

Distribution is drive-thru style. Simply pull through, provide your name and household size, and our staff will load your trunk or backseat with food.

We are excited to distribute Farmers to Families fresh food boxes that include a variety of produce, cheeses, butter, milk, and meats. We will also have some canned goods available.

SUMMER MEAL PROGRAM

The Evergreen School District will be serving our final summer meals (lunch with breakfast for the next day) at our three traditional locations TODAY, Tuesday, June 9 from 11:30-12:30.

We are excited to announce that, on weekdays June 15-August 14, a free summer meal program will serve lunch with breakfast for the next day to anyone 18 and under at three locations in Evergreen!

12:05 p.m.: Flathead County Sheriff‚Äôs Posse on Shady Lane
12:25 p.m.: Lions Park on East Evergreen Drive
12:50 p.m.: Evergreen Junior High School Cafeteria Parking Lot

We wish you all a safe, healthy, and enjoyable summer!

TODAY!!! Starting at 3:00 p.m., a Promotion Parade will be happening to honor our leaving 8th-graders. The staff parade of cars will meander through Evergreen to celebrate our promoting class. Our theme for the parade is "We Find Our Superpowers When Life Is Most Challenging." So, put on your superhero cape and come out and social distance celebrate with us! Let's help our students leave with STYLE! (Staff cars will be in the parade, and students and families may line the parade route.)

Please help us to stay healthy by social distancing from others (except your family) as you watch us drive through to honor the Evergreen Class of 2020.

post_text:
Three minute screen break

Step 1: Step away from the computer and smart phone. Go outside or stand at a window

Step 2: Scan with your eyes as far as you can see. Maintain your gaze on a far point or close your eyes for step 3-4.

Step 3: Shake your hands and arms at your sides, feeling tension leaving your body. Continue shaking and slowly raise your arms to shoulder height and above for a brief moment, then slowly return shaking arms to side of body and slow shaking until you are still.

Step 4: Belly Breathe: Take 5-9 belly breaths. Place one hand on belly and one on chest to feel that your breath fills your belly first and your chest second. Feel tension melt away with every exhale, notice particularly shoulders and jaw relaxing as many of us hold tension there. Make a sound with your exhale if it feels right and you don't care who hears :)

Step 5: Hydrate: Fill a glass with water and drink it

Step 6: Back to work: Get back to it!

Three minute screen break

Step 1: Step away from the computer and smart phone. Go outside or stand at a window

Step 2: Scan with your eyes as far as you can see. Maintain your gaze on a far point or close your eyes for step 3-4.

Step 3: Shake your hands and arms at your sides, feeling tension leaving your body. Continue shaking and slowly raise your arms to shoulder height and above for a brief moment, then slowly return shaking arms to side of body and slow shaking until you are still.

Step 4: Belly Breathe: Take 5-9 belly breaths. Place one hand on belly and one on chest to feel that your breath fills your belly first and your chest second. Feel tension melt away with every exhale, notice particularly shoulders and jaw relaxing as many of us hold tension there. Make a sound with your exhale if it feels right and you don't care who hears :)

Step 5: Hydrate: Fill a glass with water and drink it

post_text:
Remote digital learning is off to a great start in Evergreen! One of our elementary teachers sent us this message today:

‚ÄúI have been blown away by my class this week. We have been doing [Google] meets every afternoon, and these kids are amazing! We address homework questions first and then the daily focus. Today was reading, and we discussed the novels that students were reading. The kids understand norms and would mute themselves and ask to speak next through messenger. It‚Äôs pretty incredible how diverse learning can be. We then took some time to do some of the normal stuff that we do in class which is a game called ‚Äòwould you rather.‚Äô The thing that struck me the most and had me in tears was that they see this as any other classroom. We were getting to the end of our meeting one student said, ‚ÄúTomorrow is Friday. I was wondering if we could still do free write and in the afternoon if our meeting could be Author‚Äôs Chair like we always do on Friday.‚Äù

Our teachers and kids are pretty incredible!
